headlines.description: — Dyson Daniels scored 25 points, and the surging Atlanta Hawks beat the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers 132-123 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels leads balanced attack with 25 points as surging Hawks beat short-handed 76ers 132-123

headlines.description: — Sam Hauser started in place of Jayson Tatum and did what he and the Boston Celtics have done all season — shoot a bunch of 3-pointers and make more than their share.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam Hauser becomes 4th Celtics player with 9 3s in a game as Boston keeps shooting from deep

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Noah Clowney scored 19 points and the Brooklyn Nets beat Los Angeles 111-108 on Monday night in the Lakers' first game since losing <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets snap 7-game skid by beating Lakers 111-108 in first game since LeBron James' groin injury

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 35 points, Mark Williams added 24 points and 10 rebounds and the Charlotte Hornets got their first divisional win of the season by beating the reeling Miami Heat 105-102 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets rally past reeling Heat, who waste another 17-point lead in 105-102 loss

headlines.description: — Toronto native A.J. Lawson made seven 3-pointers while scoring a career-high 32 points, and he also had 12 of the Raptors' franchise-record 73 rebounds in a 119-104 victory over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toronto native A.J. Lawson paces 4 double-doubles for Raptors in 119-104 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey had a season-high 29 points along with 10 rebounds before leaving midway through the fourth quarter with a right ankle injury, and the Chicago Bulls won their third straight game, 121-103 over the Indiana Pacers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Josh Giddey scores season-high 29 points before injuring ankle and Bulls beat Pacers 121-103

headlines.description: — Jabari Smith Jr. had 20 points and tied a career high with five 3-pointers, helping the Houston Rockets beat the Orlando Magic 97-84 on Monday night for their third consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jabari Smith Jr. stars as the Rockets beat the Magic 97-84 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 29 points and 12 assists, and the Memphis Grizzlies rallied from an early 16-point deficit to beat the Phoenix Suns 120-118 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant scores 29 and Grizzlies climb out of early hole to beat Suns 120-118

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 35 points, 18 rebounds and eight assists, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 140-127 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 35 points and 18 rebounds to lead Nuggets past West-leading Thunder 140-127

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Spencer Dinwiddie scored 28 points, and the depleted Dallas Mavericks stopped a five-game slide by edging the San Antonio Spurs 133-129 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: With only 8 healthy players, Mavericks rally to defeat Spurs 133-129 to snap 5-game skid

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 24 points and moved within two 3-pointers of becoming the first player in NBA history with 4,000, Jimmy Butler had a triple-double, and the surging Golden State Warriors won their fifth straight game by beating the Portland...
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 24, Jimmy Butler gets triple-double, Warriors beat Blazers for 5th straight win

events.name: New York Knicks at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 26 points and nine rebounds, and the New York Knicks beat the Sacramento Kings 133-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Karl-Anthony Towns leads Knicks in 133-104 romp at Kings
